definition: variant of 人[ren2]/"person" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 10), occurring in 兒, 兀, 兄 etc
car/vehicle/CL:輛|辆[liang4]/machine/to shape with a lathe/Kangxi radical 159

sentences.english: Shujie was asleep in baby carriage, his mother kept watch by side.
sentences.chinese: 舒哲在婴儿车上熟睡，他的母亲守护在车边。

sentences.english: The brand name is printed on the stroller.
sentences.chinese: 品牌字样印在该婴儿车上。

sentences.english: Phyl got one wheel of the pram caught in something.
sentences.chinese: 菲儿推的婴儿车有一个轮子被什么东西夹住了。

sentences.english: The child was pushing a pram .
sentences.chinese: 这孩子正在推一辆婴儿车。

sentences.english: She loves cooking and dislikes prams .
sentences.chinese: 她喜欢烹调，不喜欢婴儿车。

sentences.english: The baby had been snatched from its pram.
sentences.chinese: 那婴儿被人从婴儿车中劫走了。

sentences.english: Your stroller (pram) has been put at the boarding gate.
sentences.chinese: 您的婴儿车已经放在登机口了。

sentences.english: What I really need to buy is a baby carriage.
sentences.chinese: 我真正需要买的是辆婴儿车。

sentences.english: It isn't just the strollers in gay neighborhoods.
sentences.chinese: 不单是说同志社区出现了婴儿车。

sentences.english: Luckily, he was strapped into his pram at the time, which probably saved his life.
sentences.chinese: 侥幸，当时，他被绑在婴儿车上，这可能救了他的命。

sentences.english: Can even be used as a sun shield for stroller.
sentences.chinese: 甚至可以作为一个婴儿车遮阳板使用。

sentences.english: Moments later, a well-to-do young woman pushing a kid in a stroller stepped into the lobby.
sentences.chinese: 不一会儿，一位年轻贵妇推着一个婴儿车走进了大厅。

sentences.english: Because of the pram in the hall.
sentences.chinese: 原因在于门厅里的婴儿车。

sentences.english: The pram had its hood folded down.
sentences.chinese: 这辆婴儿车上的折叠式布篷被收了下来。

sentences.english: You'll have that pram if you don't take more care.
sentences.chinese: 如果你不多加小心的话，会把那辆婴儿车弄翻的。

definition: empress's throne/(fig.) first place in a feminine competition
